                <div>
                        <h2>Dr. Myles Preble (Utah)</h2>
                        <p>Dr. Preble graduated from Washington University School of Dental Medicine in St. Louis Missouri in 1983. He continued his education by attending multiple advanced dental classes concentrating his energies in cosmetic/aesthetic dentistry. He graduated from a postgraduate comprehensive restorative continuum at Baylor University at Dallas, Texas in 1994. He has been advancing his clinical skills in neuromuscular dentistry since 2003 and has been applying his extensive knowledge and vast experience as a cosmetic and neuromuscular dentist to improve both the function and the appearance of the entire mouth . He has been providing custom - fitted athletic sports appliances for his two sons and their hockey teams for over twenty years. Dr. Preble takes pride in having one of the most progressive and educated offices in Utah. He is currently a member of the North American Neuromuscular Study Club, the International Academy of Oral Medicine and Toxicology, the International College of Cranio-Mandibular Orthopedics, and the American Academy of Dental Sleep Medicine. Dr. Preble is located at 6440 S. Wasatch Boulevard, Suite 140, in Salt Lake City, Utah 84121. <strong>Phone:&nbsp;(801) 278-4787. &nbsp;Email: drpreble@agilityguard.com</strong>
