                <div>
                        <h2><strong>Dr. Michael Nemec (Nova Scotia)</strong>
                        </h2>
                        <p>Dr. Michael Nemec resides and works in Port Hawkesbury, Nova Scotia, Canada. He graduated with a Bachelor of Science Degree from Acadia University in 1974 and DDS education from Dalhousie University in Halifax, Nova Scotia in 1978. </p>
                        <p>Aside from day-to-day restorative dentistry, Dr. Nemec developed interest in orthodontics and TMD therapy from the very early years of practice. The lack of success, and predictability, of symptom-free TMD therapy brought him to Gneuro-muscular concepts first introduced to him by Dr. James Carlson. Additional education followed at LVI (primarily under the tutelage of Dr. Clayton Chan) and lastly, but most profoundly, at The Occlusion Connection.</p>
                        <h3><strong class="font-size-small">Gneuro-Muscular Education:</strong>
                        </h3>
                        <ul><li><strong>Dr. J. Carlson: &nbsp;</strong>Introduction to Neuro-muscular Occlusion-Level 1 &amp; 2</li>
                        <li><strong>LVI:&nbsp;</strong>Occlusion 1, 2, 3; &nbsp;Neuro-muscular Orthodontics Levels 1, 2, 3; &nbsp;Pedodontic Neuro-muscular Orthodontics;&nbsp;TMD</li>
                        <li><strong>Occlusion Connection (Dr. Clayton Chan): &nbsp;</strong>Levels 3, 4, 5, 6, 7;&nbsp;Ortho I.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Dr. Nemec is located at 308 Philpott Street Unit 1, Port Hawkesbury, Nova Scotia B9A 2B8. <strong>Phone: 902 625-3345</strong>
                        </p>
