                <div style="float:left; margin-right:20px;" >
                      <p><img src="http://www.agilityguard.com/assets/images/system/images/0000/0427/Charlie_Kawata_Pic_medium.jpg" title="Charlie Kawata Pic" alt="Charlie Kawata Pic" rel="medium"></p>
                </div>
                <div>
                      <h2><strong>Dr. Toshimitsu "Charlie" Kawada (Tokyo)</strong>
                      </h2>
                      <span class="font-size-normal"><p>Dr. Toshimitsu "Charlie" Kawada is a graduate of the Tokyo Dental College where he has earned his Doctor of Dental Surgery degree in 1981. He has been practicing in the central part of Tokyo, Japan as a general dentist since 1984 with a special focus and interest in neuromuscular and cosmetic dentistry. Dr. Kawada has extended his aesthetic and occlusion training in the United States at the Las Vegas Institute in 1998 where he has taken three levels of neuromuscular occlusion training in addition to restorative courses in adhesive dentistry. He considers his advanced training experience a highlight in his professional career.</p>
                      <p>In 2008 he was awarded the prestigious Fellowship award from the International College of Cranio-mandibular Orthopedics (ICCMO). From 2001- 2009 he has attended annually Dr. Chan's advanced neuromuscular and occlusion seminars in Japan. He has enhanced post graduate training and skills at the training center of Occlusion Connections in Las Vegas, Nevada. He has attended the Level 5 Advanced Neuromuscular Bite Refinement and K7 Practicum with Dr. Chan where he has found that Occlusion Connections meets his dental professional continuing education and development needs.</p>
                      </span>
                      <p>Dr. Kawada is a recognized lecturer to dentist throughout Japan in the latest treatment modalities relating to cosmetic dentistry and neuromuscular occlusion. He is a past Chairman and current Administrator of ICCMO Japan a leading Neuromuscular organization focused on objective documentation and the science of the masticatory system. Dr. Kawada is located at&nbsp;1-5-31 arai building 1F  motoakasaka, Minatoku, Tokyo, Japan. <strong>Phone number  81-3-3478-1181. &nbsp;email: &nbsp;drkawada@agilityguard.com &nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;( www.ricoh-dental.com).</p>
                </div>
                <div style="clear:both;"></div>
              </div>
              
              
              
              

              <h2>Dr. Neil Zane (New York)</h2>
              <p>Dr. Neil Zane is a native New Yorker who grew up with his family in Westchester. Heading off to college in Worchester, Massachusetts, Dr. Zane graduated from Clark University in 1973 with a B.A. in Psychology. He graduated from Columbia School of Dentistry with his Doctorate in 1979.</p>
              <p>Within a year after he had earned his doctorate, Dr. Zane initiated an educational journey that continues to this day. In 1980, he completed a post-graduate program in prosthodontics. Six years later, he completed a course at the Pankey Institute in Key Biscayne, Florida, focusing on dental occlusion, its complexities, and related muscular-skeletal disorders (e.g., TMD). Between 1998 and 2001, he attended additional continuing education courses held annually at the prestigious Las Vegas Institute for Advanced Dental Studies. During this four-year period, he completed in-depth studies of aesthetics, restoration, and occlusion. Since 2003, Dr. Zane has attended numerous neuromuscular courses in implants, dentures, and orthodontics.</p>
              <p>Active in his community of professionals, Dr. Neil Zane is a Fellow in the Academy of General Dentistry (FAGD). He is also a member of the New York Academy of Dentistry, the International College of Cranial-Mandibular Orthopedics (ICCMO), the North American Neuromuscular Study Club (NANSC), and the New York County Dental Society, where he also serves as a member of its Peer Review Committee. &nbsp;Dr. Zane is located at 550 Park Avenue New York, New York 10065. &nbsp;<strong>Phone number (212) 826-0777.&nbsp;</strong>
              </p>


